[{"category":"section","location":"api/#API-Reference","page":"API Reference","text":"","title":"API Reference"},{"category":"section","location":"api/#Codebook","page":"API Reference","text":"","title":"Codebook"},{"category":"section","location":"api/#Rotation","page":"API Reference","text":"","title":"Rotation"},{"category":"section","location":"api/#MSE-Quantizer","page":"API Reference","text":"","title":"MSE Quantizer"},{"category":"section","location":"api/#Inner-Product-Quantizer","page":"API Reference","text":"","title":"Inner Product Quantizer"},{"category":"section","location":"api/#KV-Cache","page":"API Reference","text":"","title":"KV Cache"},{"category":"section","location":"api/#Nearest-Neighbor-Search","page":"API Reference","text":"","title":"Nearest Neighbor Search"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#TurboQuant.LloydMaxCodebook","page":"API Reference","text":"LloydMaxCodebook\n\nStores precomputed optimal centroids and decision boundaries for a given bit-width and target distribution (Beta distribution of rotated coordinates).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TurboQuant.LloydMaxCodebook"},{"category":"function","location":"api/#TurboQuant.solve_codebook","page":"API Reference","text":"solve_codebook(d, b; max_iter=1000, tol=1e-10, n_quad=10000)\n\nSolve the Lloyd-Max optimal quantizer for the Beta distribution arising from random rotation in dimension d, at bit-width b.\n\nReturns a LloydMaxCodebook with 2^b centroids and 2^b-1 decision boundaries.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TurboQuant.solve_codebook"},{"category":"function","location":"api/#TurboQuant.quantize_scalar","page":"API Reference","text":"quantize_scalar(val, cb::LloydMaxCodebook)\n\nQuantize a single scalar value using the precomputed codebook. Returns the index (1-based) of the nearest centroid.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TurboQuant.quantize_scalar"},{"category":"function","location":"api/#TurboQuant.dequantize_scalar","page":"API Reference","text":"dequantize_scalar(idx, cb::LloydMaxCodebook)\n\nLook up the centroid value for index idx.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TurboQuant.dequantize_scalar"},{"category":"function","location":"api/#TurboQuant.precompute_codebooks","page":"API Reference","text":"precompute_codebooks(d; max_bits=8)\n\nPrecompute Lloyd-Max codebooks for bit-widths 1 through max_bits. Returns a Dict{Int, LloydMaxCodebook}.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TurboQuant.precompute_codebooks"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#TurboQuant.RandomRotation","page":"API Reference","text":"RandomRotation\n\nDense random orthogonal rotation matrix generated via QR decomposition of a Gaussian random matrix. O(d²) storage and O(d²) multiply.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TurboQuant.RandomRotation"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#TurboQuant.HadamardRotation","page":"API Reference","text":"HadamardRotation\n\nStructured random rotation using randomized Hadamard transform: Π = D₃ H D₂ H D₁  (three rounds of Hadamard with random diagonal signs).\n\nThis achieves O(d log d) rotation instead of O(d²), with similar distributional properties for sub-Gaussian tail bounds.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TurboQuant.HadamardRotation"},{"category":"function","location":"api/#TurboQuant.rotate","page":"API Reference","text":"rotate(R::RandomRotation, x)\n\nApply forward rotation: y = Π · x. Supports vectors (d,) and matrices (d, N) for batch processing.\n\n\n\n\n\nrotate(R::HadamardRotation, x::AbstractVector)\n\nApply structured Hadamard rotation to a vector.\n\n\n\n\n\nrotate(R::HadamardRotation, X::AbstractMatrix)\n\nBatch rotation: each column is a vector to rotate.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TurboQuant.rotate"},{"category":"function","location":"api/#TurboQuant.rotate_back","page":"API Reference","text":"rotate_back(R::RandomRotation, y)\n\nApply inverse rotation: x = Π^T · y.\n\n\n\n\n\nrotate_back(R::HadamardRotation, y::AbstractVector)\n\nApply inverse structured Hadamard rotation. The inverse of Di H / √d is H Di / √d (since H and D are self-inverse up to scaling).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TurboQuant.rotate_back"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#TurboQuant.TurboQuantMSE","page":"API Reference","text":"TurboQuantMSE{R}\n\nMSE-optimal vector quantizer using:\n\nRandom rotation Π to normalize coordinate distribution\nPer-coordinate Lloyd-Max scalar quantization\nNorm preservation via separate float storage\n\nType parameter R is the rotation type (RandomRotation or HadamardRotation).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TurboQuant.TurboQuantMSE"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#TurboQuant.CompressedVectorMSE","page":"API Reference","text":"CompressedVectorMSE\n\nCompressed representation of a batch of vectors using MSE quantization.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TurboQuant.CompressedVectorMSE"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#TurboQuant.setup-Tuple{Type{TurboQuantMSE}, Int64, Int64}","page":"API Reference","text":"setup(::Type{TurboQuantMSE}, d, b; seed=UInt64(42), use_hadamard=false)\n\nInitialize the MSE quantizer for vectors of dimension d at bit-width b.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TurboQuant.setup"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#TurboQuant.quantize-Tuple{TurboQuantMSE, AbstractMatrix}","page":"API Reference","text":"quantize(tq::TurboQuantMSE, X::AbstractMatrix)\n\nQuantize a batch of vectors. X is (d, N) where each column is a vector. Returns a CompressedVectorMSE.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TurboQuant.quantize"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#TurboQuant.dequantize-Tuple{TurboQuantMSE, CompressedVectorMSE}","page":"API Reference","text":"dequantize(tq::TurboQuantMSE, comp::CompressedVectorMSE)\n\nDequantize a compressed representation back to approximate vectors. Returns a (d, N) matrix.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TurboQuant.dequantize"},{"category":"function","location":"api/#TurboQuant.compression_ratio","page":"API Reference","text":"compression_ratio(comp::CompressedVectorMSE)\n\nCompute the compression ratio relative to Float64 storage.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TurboQuant.compression_ratio"},{"category":"function","location":"api/#TurboQuant.mse_distortion","page":"API Reference","text":"mse_distortion(tq::TurboQuantMSE, X::AbstractMatrix)\n\nCompute the mean squared error of quantize→dequantize roundtrip.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TurboQuant.mse_distortion"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#TurboQuant.TurboQuantProd","page":"API Reference","text":"TurboQuantProd{R}\n\nUnbiased inner product quantizer using two-stage pipeline:\n\nTurboQuant_MSE at (b-1) bits for base approximation\nQJL (Quantized Johnson-Lindenstrauss) 1-bit projection on residual\n\nGuarantees E[⟨y, x̃⟩] = ⟨y, x⟩ (unbiased inner product estimation).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TurboQuant.TurboQuantProd"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#TurboQuant.CompressedVectorProd","page":"API Reference","text":"CompressedVectorProd\n\nCompressed representation using the two-stage prod quantizer.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TurboQuant.CompressedVectorProd"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#TurboQuant.setup-Tuple{Type{TurboQuantProd}, Int64, Int64}","page":"API Reference","text":"setup(::Type{TurboQuantProd}, d, b; seed=UInt64(42), seed_qjl=UInt64(123), use_hadamard=false)\n\nInitialize the unbiased inner product quantizer. Uses (b-1) bits for MSE stage + 1 bit for QJL residual stage. Requires b ≥ 2.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TurboQuant.setup"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#TurboQuant.quantize-Tuple{TurboQuantProd, AbstractMatrix}","page":"API Reference","text":"quantize(tq::TurboQuantProd, X::AbstractMatrix)\n\nTwo-stage quantization:\n\nMSE quantize at (b-1) bits\nCompute residual, apply QJL (sign of random projection)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TurboQuant.quantize"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#TurboQuant.dequantize-Tuple{TurboQuantProd, CompressedVectorProd}","page":"API Reference","text":"dequantize(tq::TurboQuantProd, comp::CompressedVectorProd)\n\nTwo-stage dequantization: x̃ = x̃mse + √(π/2)/d · ‖r‖ · S^T · qjlsigns\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TurboQuant.dequantize"},{"category":"function","location":"api/#TurboQuant.inner_product","page":"API Reference","text":"inner_product(tq::TurboQuantProd, comp::CompressedVectorProd, y::AbstractVector)\n\nCompute approximate inner products ⟨x̃_i, y⟩ for all quantized vectors, without full dequantization. Returns a vector of length N.\n\nThis is unbiased: E[result] = ⟨x, y⟩ for each vector.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TurboQuant.inner_product"},{"category":"function","location":"api/#TurboQuant.inner_product_bias","page":"API Reference","text":"inner_product_bias(tq::TurboQuantProd, X::AbstractMatrix, y::AbstractVector; n_trials=100)\n\nEstimate the bias of inner product estimation by repeated quantization. Returns (meanbias, stdbias) where bias = estimatedip - trueip.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TurboQuant.inner_product_bias"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#TurboQuant.KVCache","page":"API Reference","text":"KVCache{R}\n\nQuantized KV cache for transformer attention. Supports:\n\nOnline streaming quantization (no calibration needed)\nMixed-precision: outlier channels get extra bits\nOn-the-fly dequantization during attention computation\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TurboQuant.KVCache"},{"category":"function","location":"api/#TurboQuant.compress_kv!","page":"API Reference","text":"compress_kv!(cache::KVCache, K::AbstractMatrix, V::AbstractMatrix)\n\nAdd a new token's K and V to the cache with online quantization. K, V are (headdim, nheads) — one vector per attention head.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TurboQuant.compress_kv!"},{"category":"function","location":"api/#TurboQuant.attention_with_quantized_kv","page":"API Reference","text":"attention_with_quantized_kv(cache::KVCache, Q::AbstractMatrix;\n                             scale=nothing)\n\nCompute attention output using quantized KV cache. Q is (headdim, nheads) for the current query token.\n\nComputes: output = softmax(Q^T K / √d) V  using quantized K and V. Returns (headdim, nheads) output.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TurboQuant.attention_with_quantized_kv"},{"category":"function","location":"api/#TurboQuant.memory_usage","page":"API Reference","text":"memory_usage(cache::KVCache)\n\nEstimate memory usage of the quantized KV cache in bytes.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TurboQuant.memory_usage"},{"category":"function","location":"api/#TurboQuant.fp16_memory_usage","page":"API Reference","text":"fp16_memory_usage(cache::KVCache)\n\nMemory usage if KV cache were stored in Float16.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TurboQuant.fp16_memory_usage"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#TurboQuant.TurboQuantIndex","page":"API Reference","text":"TurboQuantIndex{R}\n\nA nearest neighbor search index using TurboQuant compression. No codebook learning required — vectors are quantized online using random rotation + Lloyd-Max quantization.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TurboQuant.TurboQuantIndex"},{"category":"function","location":"api/#TurboQuant.build_index","page":"API Reference","text":"build_index(X::AbstractMatrix, bit_width::Int;\n            seed=UInt64(42), use_hadamard=true, batch_size=1000)\n\nBuild a nearest neighbor search index from database vectors. X is (d, N) where each column is a database vector.\n\nThis is essentially instantaneous compared to PQ (no k-means training).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TurboQuant.build_index"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#TurboQuant.search-Tuple{TurboQuantIndex, AbstractVector, Int64}","page":"API Reference","text":"search(index::TurboQuantIndex, query::AbstractVector, k::Int)\n\nFind the k approximate nearest neighbors of query in the index. Returns (indices, scores) where indices are 1-based into the original database and scores are approximate inner products (higher = more similar).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TurboQuant.search"},{"category":"function","location":"api/#TurboQuant.batch_search","page":"API Reference","text":"batch_search(index::TurboQuantIndex, queries::AbstractMatrix, k::Int)\n\nSearch for k nearest neighbors for each query column in queries. Returns (indicesmatrix, scoresmatrix) each of size (k, n_queries).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TurboQuant.batch_search"},{"category":"function","location":"api/#TurboQuant.recall_at_k","page":"API Reference","text":"recall_at_k(index::TurboQuantIndex, queries::AbstractMatrix,\n            ground_truth::AbstractMatrix, k::Int)\n\nCompute recall@1@k: fraction of queries where the true nearest neighbor is among the top-k results from the approximate search.\n\nground_truth is (1, n_queries) containing the index of each query's true NN.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"TurboQuant.recall_at_k"},{"category":"section","location":"#TurboQuant.jl","page":"Home","text":"A Julia implementation of advanced vector quantization based on TurboQuant (arXiv:2504.19874v1).\n\nAchieves near information-theoretically optimal compression without any calibration data or codebook learning.","title":"TurboQuant.jl"},{"category":"section","location":"#Key-Features","page":"Home","text":"Online / data-oblivious — no preprocessing, calibration, or codebook learning required\nNear-optimal distortion — within 2.72× of Shannon's lower bound\nUnbiased inner products — critical for attention mechanisms and nearest-neighbor search\nFully vectorizable — designed for GPU/TPU-friendly execution","title":"Key Features"},{"category":"section","location":"#Installation","page":"Home","text":"using Pkg\nPkg.add(\"TurboQuant\")","title":"Installation"},{"category":"section","location":"#Quick-Start","page":"Home","text":"","title":"Quick Start"},{"category":"section","location":"#MSE-Quantizer","page":"Home","text":"using TurboQuant\nusing LinearAlgebra\n\nd = 128    # vector dimension\nb = 4      # bits per coordinate\ntq = setup(TurboQuantMSE, d, b)\n\nx = randn(d)                          # original vector\ncomp = quantize(tq, x)                # compress\nx_hat = dequantize(tq, comp)          # decompress\nprintln(\"MSE: \", sum((x .- x_hat[:,1]).^2) / d)","title":"MSE Quantizer"},{"category":"section","location":"#Batch-Quantization","page":"Home","text":"X = randn(d, 1000)                    # 1000 vectors\ncomp = quantize(tq, X)\nX_hat = dequantize(tq, comp)","title":"Batch Quantization"},{"category":"section","location":"#Unbiased-Inner-Product-Quantizer","page":"Home","text":"tq_prod = setup(TurboQuantProd, d, 4)\ncomp = quantize(tq_prod, X)\ny = randn(d)\napprox_ips = inner_product(tq_prod, comp, y)   # E[result] = X' * y (unbiased)","title":"Unbiased Inner Product Quantizer"},{"category":"section","location":"#Nearest-Neighbor-Search","page":"Home","text":"index = build_index(X, 4; use_hadamard=true)\nindices, scores = search(index, y, 10)","title":"Nearest Neighbor Search"},{"category":"section","location":"#KV-Cache","page":"Home","text":"cache = KVCache(8, 64, 3; max_seq_len=131072)\nK = randn(64, 8); V = randn(64, 8)\ncompress_kv!(cache, K, V)\nQ = randn(64, 8)\noutput = attention_with_quantized_kv(cache, Q)","title":"KV Cache"},{"category":"section","location":"#References","page":"Home","text":"Zandieh, Daliri, Hadian, Mirrokni. TurboQuant: Online Vector Quantization for Near-Optimal Quantized Retrieval, KV Cache Quantization, and Beyond. arXiv:2504.19874v1, April 2025.","title":"References"}]
